# Source-keeper — source quality profile

_Last updated: (date) by (you or source-keeper)_

The source-keeper reads this before every run and updates it from feedback.
You can edit it by hand at any time; keep it under ~150 lines.

## What makes a good source here

- (e.g. posts actual dates and locations, not just social-media teasers)
- (e.g. updates at least weekly)
- (e.g. covers the region specifically, not the whole state)

## Sources to avoid

- (e.g. content-farm "things to do" aggregators that recycle old listings)

## Learned preferences

(Dated bullets appended by the agent, citing which sources produced
loved/hated finds.)

## Standing instructions

- Keep one note per site in notes/sites/<host>.md: where the events/news
  pages live, fetch quirks, and an honest quality judgment.
- Mark sources dead rather than deleting them; note why.
